# No Git Commit or Push

Do not commit or push anything to git in this project.

- Never run `git commit`, `git push`, or equivalent commands.
- Never create commits, even if the user asks you to.
- Never push to remote, even if the user asks you to.
- You may still use read-only git commands (e.g. `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`) when needed to inspect the repository.

If the user wants changes committed or pushed, tell them to do it themselves locally.
